    "description": "The strategy is a simple time series momentum or trend following overlay applied across major asset class ETFs, going long only when price is above a long term moving average. It targets persistent directional trends and attempts to avoid prolonged drawdowns by holding risk assets primarily during positive trend regimes, using a 210 trading day simple moving average (approximately 10 months) computed on daily data as the regime filter.\n\nThe investable universe is a fixed set of liquid US listed ",
    "description_full": "The strategy is a simple time series momentum or trend following overlay applied across major asset class ETFs, going long only when price is above a long term moving average. It targets persistent directional trends and attempts to avoid prolonged drawdowns by holding risk assets primarily during positive trend regimes, using a 210 trading day simple moving average (approximately 10 months) computed on daily data as the regime filter.\n\nThe investable universe is a fixed set of liquid US listed ETFs representing US equities (SPY), developed ex US equities (EFA), US bonds (BND), US REITs (VNQ), and broad commodities (GSG). Each trading day, for each ETF with a ready SMA, the strategy issues a one day long signal if the ETF close is above its SMA; ETFs not meeting the filter receive no long signal and are effectively held at zero weight. Portfolio construction equal weights all currently eligible long positions, rebalancing as signals change, with immediate execution. There are no explicit risk management overlays, volatility scaling, leverage controls, stop losses, or drawdown limits beyond the implicit de risking that occurs when an ETF falls below its moving average.",
